Description: Hange discovers that Krista is the true heir to the throne, but before she can be installed as queen, she is kidnapped.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 15
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: In this series, which is based on the 2014 animated film, Hiro investigates the disappearance of his brother Tadashi, with help from his robot, Baymax.
Title: BIG HERO 6, VOL. 1
Author: Haruki Ueno

Description: As this series barrels toward its conclusion, Naruto and Sasuke must work together to defeat Madara.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 69
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: A teenager signs up to help mythical creatures assimilate into society. How will he contend being roommates with a sexy snake woman, an alluring centaur girl and a harpy who likes to flirt?
Title: MONSTER MUSUME, VOL. 6
Author: Okayado

Description: The final volume is here. Who will emerge victorious: Kishin or Shinigami?
Title: SOUL EATER VOL. 25
Author: Atsushi Ohkubo

Description: Kirito has escaped from the virtual reality world of Sword Art Online, but now, he must go inside another game to try and save the woman he loves.
Title: SWORD ART ONLINE: FAIRY DANCE, VOL. 3
Author: Reki Kawahara and Tsubasa Haduki
Contributor: by Reki Kawahara and Tsubasa Haduki

Description: A soldier battles aliens over and over on the same day in this adaptation of the science fiction novel, upon which the film “Edge of Tomorrow” is based.
Title: ALL YOU NEED IS KILL
Author: Hiroshi Sakurazaka, Ryosuke Takeuchi and Takeshi Obata
Contributor: by Hiroshi Sakurazaka, Ryosuke Takeuchi and Takeshi Obata

Description: Is this the end of humanity? It sure looks that way when what is left of mankind must go into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: Yuichiro is on a mission to kill every vampire in existence but in order to accomplish his goal, he must become a master of demon–possessed weaponry.
Title: SERAPH OF THE END, VOL. 4
Author: Takaya Kagami and Yamato Yamamoto
Contributor: by Takaya Kagami and Yamato Yamamoto

Description: The students of class 3–E have only one assignment: kill the teacher! Of course, when that teacher is also a supremely powerful being, it is easier said than done.
Title: ASSASSINATION CLASSROOM, VOL. 2
Author: Yusei Matsui
